        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 5:17PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 517 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm just
northeast of Westcliffe, or 45 miles west of Pueblo, moving east at
5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Silver Cliff, Westcliffe, and Rosita.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
